data-triple-N3.o: "Blackburn Rovers Football Club is an English professional association football club based in the town of Blackburn, Lancashire. The team competes in the Football League Championship from the 201213 season. They were relegated from the Premier League, the top tier of English football, at the end of the 201112 season. The club are currently without a manager after sacking manager Michael Appleton on 19 March 2013, the third manager to lost his job in 6 months after Steve Kean and Henning Berg."@en
